					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13418030#post-4713902</guid>
				<title>Re: -1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13418030/scp-5907#post-4713902</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2020 07:11:01 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Whalerus</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3305725</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I did +1 but you have a point here. I think it would improve the scip if the video log was moved closer to the end, perhaps by combining the discovery section with parts of the incident report. Ideally I think the scip should end with at most a short paragraph after the video log. The incident report really only adds the fact that the bodies disintegrated into denim clothes when moved and that all that was left was stuffing and bones.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13418030#post-4682856</guid>
				<title>-1</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13418030/scp-5907#post-4682856</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2020 20:52:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rounderhouse</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4187885</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This article is basically reliant on the log, and the log fails to carry it. The dialogue is stilted and expository &#8212; the details of their transformation are good, but there better ways to get that kind of imagery and detail across than in a video log. The ending isn't a stinger because everyone sees it coming when they realize what the anomaly does.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
